Class MilStdSymbol

  • java.lang.Object
    • mil.emp3.api.abstracts.Container
      • mil.emp3.api.abstracts.Feature<IGeoMilSymbol>
        • mil.emp3.api.MilStdSymbol
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IContainer, IFeature<IGeoMilSymbol>, IGeoAltitudeMode, IGeoBase, IGeoContainer, IGeoMilSymbol, IGeoPositionGroup, IGeoRenderable

    public class MilStdSymbol
extends Feature<IGeoMilSymbol>
implements IGeoMilSymbol
    This class encapsulates a GeoMilSymbol. It provides additional functionality.

    • Constructor Detail

      • MilStdSymbol

        public MilStdSymbol()
        This is the default constructor for the class. It creates a GeoMilSymbol that is rendered using the standard MilStd 2525 coloring scheme. Setting the stroke, fill, and or label styles will alter the colors the symbol is rendered in.

      • MilStdSymbol

        public MilStdSymbol(IGeoMilSymbol.SymbolStandard eStandard,
                    java.lang.String sSymbolCode)
             throws EMP_Exception
        This constructor creates MilStdSymbol, and sets the MilStd version and symbol code to the values provided. It creates a GeoMilSymbol that is rendered using the standard MilStd 2525 coloring scheme. Setting the stroke, fill, and or label styles will alter the colors the symbol is rendered in.
        Parameters:
        eStandard - IGeoMilSymbol.SymbolStandard
        sSymbolCode - A valid MilStd symbol code.
        Throws:
        EMP_Exception

      • MilStdSymbol

        public MilStdSymbol(IGeoMilSymbol oRenderable)
             throws EMP_Exception
        This constructor creates MilStdSymbol from the the IGeoMilSymbol object provided. If the standard version is not set, it is set to the default value. If the modifiers are null it is set to an empty modifier list.
        Parameters:
        oRenderable - an object that implements the IGeoMilSymbol interface.
        Throws:
        EMP_Exception - This exception is raised if the geo renderable provided has an invalid symbol code.

      • setIconScale

        public void setIconScale(double dScale)
        This method sets the icon scale. It only applies to single point MilStd symbols. The size of the icon will be modified by this factor when rendered.
        Parameters:
        dScale - A value smaller than 1.0 decreases the size. A value larger than 1.0 increases the size.
